/- Wikifunctions Z30840 "arithmetic mean of Natural numbers as Rational" вЂ” Wikidata Q19033.
    The function takes a finite collection of natural numbers and returns their arithmetic
    mean exactly as a Rational number: (aв‚Ѓ + в‹Ї + aв‚™) / n.

    NOTE on primary_decl: `MeasureTheory.average` (Mathlib.MeasureTheory.Integral.Average)
    is the NONCOMPUTABLE Bochner integral average of a function over a measure вЂ” a
    wrong_target for this elementary listв†’в„љ mean. The faithful oracle is built from the
    computable primitives `List.sum` (cast to в„љ) and division in в„љ; it is fully computable.
    The empty-list convention here returns 0 (matching `x / 0 = 0` in в„љ); a real
    implementation may instead reject the empty input. -/
namespace Z30840

/-- Oracle: arithmetic mean of a list of naturals, as a rational. Computable over в„љ. -/
def spec (l : List в„•) : в„љ :=
  ((l.map (Nat.cast : в„• в†’ в„љ)).sum) / (l.length : в„љ)

/-- Concrete sanity check: mean of [1,2,3,4] = 10/4 = 5/2. -/
